{"ts":"2026-06-03T23:24:08.579Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-haak"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"File-backed schema sections (types/statuses/fields/type_workflows) leak into settings.json on writeSettings"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"readSettings merges file-backed schema sections from schema/types.json, schema/statuses.json, schema/fields.json and schema/workflows.json into the resolved settings object (settings.item_types.definitions and settings.schema.statuses/fields/type_workflows). Because callers like `pm config set` read via that merged object and then call writeSettings(settings), serializeSettings persists the MERGED schema back into settings.json. After that, editing or DELETING a rule in the schema/*.json file is silently ignored, because the stale copy baked into settings.json remains active (settings.json + file merge keeps the stale settings entry)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:config","area:schema","data-durability","living-map"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-03T23:24:08.579Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-03T23:24:08.579Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/value","value":"Pre-existing data-integrity bug surfaced during PR #106 (Codex review). Affects all file-backed schema sections; extended to type_workflows by the per-type workflow feature. Without it, file-driven schema customization (the documented workflow) becomes unreliable after any settings write."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-8jdc"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"376ea0cbea12a5afe49a65b411bd61e